The paper deals with integrity constraints and actions to restore consistency in knowledge bases, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also applies the methodology to ontologies, which fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The iterative algorithms mentioned in the abstract suggest a software engineering (cs.SE) aspect to the paper. Finally, the use of repair suggestions in the integrity constraints implies a programming languages (cs.PL) perspective.
